verbose_text: The increase in cAMP levels brought about by AAT activation of adenylate cyclase and classic downstream activation of cyclic AMP dependent protein kinase (PKA) by cAMP can inhibit endotoxin stimulated TNF-alpha and IL-10 production in human monocytes [XREF_BIBR].
